<Content>Comfortable  I can see how one could have a high quality stay here, but our stay was far from exceptional. As per the other reviews, the positives are:- clean, comfortable rooms with double windows you can open- friendly, helpful staff- good quality restaurant in the building- in a fun, seemingly safe areaThe negatives are:- no a/c (a problem if streetside)- on a very busy street (requiring choice between hot or noisy room)Also, the weekend we stayed had a local festival in the street on one evening, which we didn't know about and the hotel didn't let us know at all - we arrived back from a long day's cycling and walking to find a street party (loads of drunk folk, broken bottles and thunderous dance music) which wouldn't have been a problem if it wasn't such a surprise and we could have planned for it! 
