<Author>A TripAdvisor Member
<Content>Most ideal hotel My husband and I stayed at the Riehmers Hofgarten in November for three nights and had a most enjoyable time. The room was huge, stylish and comfortable. The service was exceptional. The front desk staff was most helpful in planning our itinerary. The restaurant, very classy, serves excellent cuisine. As for the hotel's location, it's perfect - 8 min walk to the underground station, and in the middle of all the sightseeing, such as the Brandenburg Gate, Potsdamerplatz, the shopping thoroughfare Kurf眉rstendamm, Checkpoint Charlie and the Jewish Museum. There is a Catholic church right beside the hotel. The room rate is most reasonble - 138 Euro a night, considering it's Berlin. We would highly recommend this hotel. 
